# Just because I am so forgetful and for the benefits of new joiners/junior developers

## Quick start on a new project ##

1. Check python version 
python --version

2. Check django version
python -c "import django; print(django.get_version())"

3. Install/Start virtual env on Win7
pip install virtualenvwrapper-win
mkvirtualenv myproject
workon myproject (when you need to activate your virtual env)

4. Install django 
pip install Django

5. Create the site
django-admin startproject mysite

6. Create functional test
Selenuim -> webdriver etc. etc.

7. Create .gitignore
echo "db.sqlite3" >> .gitignore
echo "*.pyc" >> .gitignore

8. Git initialization
git init .
git add .
(only if there is any unwanted .pyc files) git rm -r --cached mysite/*.pyc
git commit -am "First commit"

9. Create repository in GitHub
No need to add README.md 
See https://help.github.com/articles/adding-an-existing-project-to-github-using-the-command-line/

10. Add remote origin
git remote add origin https://github.com/jchow/mysite.git

11. Push changes to git
git push -u origin master



